<br />OK, new tack without the piracy overtone: How does one build Lock-On style devices that perform the equivalent of IPS patches, into which one plugs "the real deal"? Codemasters did it for <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Game_Genie#SNES" class="postlink">Game Genie</a>, and Sega did it for <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sonic_%26_Knuckles#Lock-on_technology" class="postlink">Sonic &amp; Knuckles</a>.

		

